  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "On Windows, the default location of the roaming profile folder is `C:\\Users\\UserName\\AppData\\Roaming`.  However, this is configurable and it is not uncommon for users to move it either to secondary drives or in the case of a corporate network a network file server.\r\n\r\nInstead, the folder should be located using the `APPDATA` environment variable or the Windows API which will follow the folder wherever it goes.\r\n\r\nIf #2237 is accepted then `LOCALAPPDATA` environment variable should be used instead, which points at `C:\\Users\\UserName\\AppData\\Local` by default, but can also move (often it is placed on a secondary local hard drive or SSD separate from the OS).\r\n\r\nCode: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/common/path.go#L82\r\n",
